STORAGE.name: CounterLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies the base location of counters for properties with type is %Library.Counter. Normally this would be a global reference such as ^User.PersonC. The global reference can also include one or more leading subscripts.

STORAGE.name: DataLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies expression that is the location where data is stored for this class. Normally this would be a global reference such as ^User.PersonD. The global reference can also include one or more leading subscripts.

STORAGE.name: DefaultData
STORAGE.description: Specifies the name of the DATA definition that the Class Compiler Data Structure Generator uses to place any previously unstored properties. A property is unstored if it is storable, but is not listed in any DATA definition.

STORAGE.name: Deprecated
STORAGE.description: True if this storage is deprecated.

STORAGE.name: ExtentLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies the base location of globals used by the extent of this class.

STORAGE.name: Final
STORAGE.description: Specifies that the storage definition cannot be modified by subclasses.

STORAGE.name: IdFunction
STORAGE.description: Specifies the system function used to allocate new id values.

STORAGE.name: IdLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies location of the ID Counter.

STORAGE.name: IndexLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies the global used for indices for this class. If not specified, the index location is ^MyApp.MyClassI, where MyApp.MyClass is the classname.

STORAGE.name: Internal
STORAGE.description: If true then do not display this item in automatic documentation.

STORAGE.name: Name
STORAGE.description: Specifies the name of the Storage definition. This name must be a valid class member name and must not conflict with any other class member names.

STORAGE.name: Partitioned
STORAGE.description: Value of the Partitioned keyword

STORAGE.name: Sharded
STORAGE.description: Value of the Sharded keyword

STORAGE.name: ShardLocalClassName
STORAGE.description: Specifies the name of the shard-local class

STORAGE.name: ShardLocalTableName
STORAGE.description: Specifies the name of the shard-local table

STORAGE.name: SqlRowIdName
STORAGE.description: Specifies the name of the Row ID column projected to SQL.

STORAGE.name: SqlRowIdProperty
STORAGE.description: Specifies the SQL RowId property. This keyword is only used by classes that have been migrated from earlier InterSystems products.

STORAGE.name: SqlTableNumber
STORAGE.description: Specifies the internal SQL Table Number. This keyword is only used by classes that have been migrated from earlier InterSystems products.

STORAGE.name: State
STORAGE.description: For a serial embedded class, this keyword specifies which Data definition is used to define the serialized state of the object. This is also the default DATA definition that unstored properties will be added to by the default structure generator.

STORAGE.name: StreamLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies the default global used to store any stream properties within this class. If not specified, the index location is ^MyApp.MyClassS, where MyApp.MyClass is the classname.

STORAGE.name: Type
STORAGE.description: Specifies the Storage Class used to provide persistence for this class.

STORAGE.name: VersionLocation
STORAGE.description: Specifies location of the %Version Counter.

STORAGEDATA.name: ColumnarGlobal
STORAGEDATA.description: Specifies the name of the global this Columnar column is stored in.

STORAGEDATA.name: ConversionTarget
STORAGEDATA.description: For columnar maps, specifies that this map is the target of a storage type conversion

STORAGEDATA.name: DataDefinitionLocation
STORAGEDATA.description: Specifies the name of the global to store this field in.

STORAGEDATA.name: Name
STORAGEDATA.description: Specifies the name of the StorageData definition. This name must be a valid storage member name and must not conflict with any other StorageData names.

STORAGEDATA.name: SmallChunkSize
STORAGEDATA.description: Specifies the size of the small chunk for this colmnar string field.

STORAGEDATA.name: Structure
STORAGEDATA.description: Specifies how the data is stored into a global node.

STORAGEDATAVALUE.name: Name
STORAGEDATAVALUE.description: Specifies the name of the StorageDataValue. This name must be a valid storage member name and must not conflict with any other StorageDataValue names.

STORAGEPARTITIONKEY.name: Name
STORAGEPARTITIONKEY.description: Specifies the name of the partition key

STORAGEPARTITIONKEY.name: Properties
STORAGEPARTITIONKEY.description: Specifies the properties of the partition key

STORAGESHARDKEY.name: CoshardWith
STORAGESHARDKEY.description: Specifies the class with which to coshard this class

STORAGESHARDKEY.name: Name
STORAGESHARDKEY.description: Specifies the name of the shard key

STORAGESHARDKEY.name: Properties
STORAGESHARDKEY.description: Specifies the properties of the shard key

STORAGESQLMAP.name: Type
STORAGESQLMAP.description: Specifies what kind of a map this is.
